			    STPJS 309</div>
  <p class="std">Many men will say, &ldquo;I will never forsake you,<span class="footRef">1</span> but will stand by you<span class="footRef">2</span> at all times.&rdquo;  But the
  moment you teach them<span class="footRef">3</span> some of the mysteries of the kingdom of God<span class="footRef">4</span> that are retained in the
  heavens<span class="footRef">5</span> and are to be revealed to the children of men<span class="footRef">6</span> when they are prepared for them they will
  be the first to stone you<span class="footRef">7</span> and put you to death.<span class="footRef">8</span> It was this same principle that crucified the Lord
  Jesus Christ, and will cause the people to kill the prophets in this generation.</p>
  <p class="std">Many things are insoluble to the children of men<span class="footRef">9</span> in the last days: for instance, that God should
  raise the dead,<span class="footRef">10</span> and forgetting that things have been hid from before the foundation of the world,<span class="footRef">11</span>
  which are to be revealed to babes in the last days.<span class="footRef">12</span></p>
  <div class="topic">Some Men &ldquo;Too Wise to Be Taught&rdquo;</div>
  <p class="std">There are a great many wise men and women too in our midst who are too wise to be taught;<span class="footRef">13</span>
  therefore they must die in their ignorance,<span class="footRef">14</span> and in the resurrection they will find their mistake.<span class="footRef">15</span>
  Many seal up the door of heaven<span class="footRef">16</span> by saying, So far God may reveal and I will believe.</p>
  <p class="std">All men who become heirs of God and joint heirs with Jesus Christ<span class="footRef">17</span> will have to receive the
  fulness of the ordinances<span class="footRef">18</span> of his kingdom; and those who will not receive all the ordinances<span class="footRef">19</span> will
  come short<span class="footRef">20</span> of the fullness of that glory,<span class="footRef">21</span> if they do not lose the whole.</p>
  <div class="topic">Paradise</div>
  <p class="std">I will say something about the spirits in prison.<span class="footRef">22</span> There has been much said by modern divines
  about the words of Jesus (when on the cross) to the thief, saying, &ldquo;This day shalt thou be with me
  in paradise.&rdquo;<span class="footRef">23</span> King James&rsquo; translators make it out to say paradise. But what is paradise? It is a
  modern word: it does not answer at all to the original word that Jesus made use of. Find the original
  of the word paradise. You may as easily find a needle in a haymow. Here is a chance for battle, ye
  learned men. There is nothing in the original word in Greek from which this was taken that signifies
  paradise; but it was&mdash;This day thou shalt be with me in the world of spirits:<span class="footRef">24</span> then I will teach you
  all about it and answer your inquiries. And Peter says he went and preached to the world of spirits
  (spirits in prison, 1 Peter, 3rd chap. 19th verse),<span class="footRef">25</span> so that they who would receive it could have it
  answered by proxy by those who live on the earth,<span class="footRef">26</span> etc.</p>
